==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[mona|mōna]] + [[dæg|dæġ]].  Corresponding to Old Frisian [[monendei|mōnendei]], Old High German [[manotag|mānotag]] (Dutch [[maandag]], German [[Montag]]), Old Norse [[manadagr|mánadagr]] (Swedish [[måndag]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mo:nandæj/

===Noun===
'''mōnandæġ''' ''m''
# [[Monday]]


